sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K376015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Lux dependent RFP Generator followed by a weak constitutive LuxR generator. This was used for testing the effect of different concentrations of AHL on the this Lux promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Anisha Katyal, Andrew Kirk, Erik McCann, Lauren Rossi, Becky Hennessey

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K376008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This device uses a luxR induced cI repressed promoter (K091107) to generate RFP. The sequence for the lucx promoter is different from the specified sequence (See K091107 page) and did not respond will to AHL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The promoter sequence does not match the registry specified sequence
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Anisha Katyal, Andrew Kirk, Erik McCann, Lauren Rossi, Becky Hennessey

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K376013
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Weak LuxR generator. The J23108 sequence is different from the specified sequence (see that page for more information).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Anisha Katyal, Andrew Kirk, Erik McCann, Lauren Rossi, Becky Hennessey

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K091107
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: this part comes from LuxR promoter and cI lambda promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This hybrid promoter is designed to respond to activation by LuxR when it is bound to AHL and to repression by the phage lambda cI repressor. The repression needs to win over activation.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part is based on the idea of replacing the region of the Lux promoter downstream of the -35 with the OR2 cI half-operator, added LuxR-10 region. Based on what we have found up to now, promoters which are constructed just by inserting OR1/2 downstream of Lux are all very leaky.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Xiao Zhu

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K376010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The source for luxR was the registry
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a translational unit comprised of the Lux regulatory protein with a strong RBS (B0034) ahead of it.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The RBS was added using PCR primer extension.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Anisha Katyal, Andrew Kirk, Erik McCann, Lauren Rossi, Becky Hennessey

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFP1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Built by Josh as an intermediate in screening plasmid construction.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: jkm

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFP1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: **highly** engineered mutant of red fluorescent protein from Discosoma striata (coral)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Campbell et al., PNAS v99 p7877 URL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: monomeric RFP: Red Fluorescent Protein. Excitation peak: 584 nm Emission peak: 607 nm
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
TAATAA double stop codon added (DE).
Four silent mutations made to remove three EcoRI sites and one PstI site: A28G, A76G, A349G, G337A.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy
